body.text: Initialize the library. Needs to be called first.
Light up specified LED (1-16, LED #0 is on the side). Use `colors->black` to turn it off.
This library simulates [Engduino board] (http://www.engduino.org/). You play with it as it is, but you can also export simple TouchDevelop scripts to run on the actual board.
* Write a script which references this library (or use one of the existing ones)
* Go to `[script properties]` (click on the name of the script, next to the `[publish]` button, in code editor)
When exporting to the board most TouchDevelop APIs will not work. Only use the ones defined in this library, or the ones which are mentioned here.
You can use `senses->acceleration quick` and friends. These will work on the board. Additionally, you can use `code->button pressed` and `code->button was pressed`.
After initialization place this in your `gameloop` event.
Returns the number of milliseconds since the device booted up.
Returns the number of microseconds since the device booted up.
Returns true if the button is currently pressed.
Returns true if the button was pressed since the last time this function was called.
